CONCLUSION AND REFERENCES

5.1 Conclusion
In conclusion, JobGenie represents a significant advancement in job search technology, leveraging modern web development practices and AI capabilities. The platform successfully addresses key challenges in the job search process through intelligent matching algorithms, streamlined application tracking, and personalized recommendations. Built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, and Node.js), JobGenie demonstrates how modern technologies can be effectively combined to create a powerful job search platform.

5.2 System Specifications

5.2.1 Hardware Requirements
The system requires the following hardware specifications:

Development Environment:
- Processor: Intel Core i5 or higher
- RAM: 8GB minimum
- Storage: 256GB SSD
- Network: High-speed internet connection

Production Server:
- Cloud-based hosting
- Scalable resources
- Minimum 16GB RAM
- SSD storage

Client Requirements:
- Any modern computer or mobile device
- Internet connection
- Web browser support
- Basic input devices

5.2.2 Software Requirements

Frontend Technologies:
- React.js 18.x
- TypeScript 4.x
- Tailwind CSS
- Vite build tool

Backend Technologies:
- Node.js 16.x or higher
- Express.js framework
- MongoDB 5.x
- REST API architecture

Development Tools:
- Visual Studio Code
- Git version control
- npm package manager
- Docker containerization

Testing Tools:
- Jest for unit testing
- Cypress for E2E testing
- Chrome DevTools
- Postman for API testing

5.3 Limitations of the System

Current limitations include:

1. Performance Constraints
- Heavy load during peak job search times
- Large dataset processing delays
- Real-time update limitations

2. Technical Limitations
- Browser compatibility issues
- Mobile responsiveness challenges
- API rate limits
- Search algorithm optimization needs

3. Feature Limitations
- Limited integration with some job boards
- Basic recommendation system
- Manual resume parsing requirements
- Limited analytics capabilities

